04:24.657 --> 04:26.292
[Gasps]

04:27.060 --> 04:28.256
What are you doing?

04:29.039 --> 04:30.856
I was gonna ask you a question.

04:31.981 --> 04:35.104
Uh... you could have knocked.

04:35.602 --> 04:36.912
I didn't want to wake you.

04:39.303 --> 04:40.343
Okay.

04:42.168 --> 04:43.592
It's about confession.

04:43.943 --> 04:44.928
What about it?

04:46.368 --> 04:47.559
What do you do?

04:50.517 --> 04:55.586
You confess your sins,
and the priest gives you penance

04:55.655 --> 04:57.992
so you can atone,
and then you're absolved.

05:00.860 --> 05:01.741
Does it work?

05:04.720 --> 05:06.287
Not for everything.

05:07.300 --> 05:10.635
♪

05:13.167 --> 05:14.488
I didn't mean to scare you.

05:14.874 --> 05:19.210
♪

05:25.618 --> 05:28.252
Woman: Adam! Adam! Adam! Adam!

05:28.321 --> 05:29.420
Adam! Adam! Adam!

05:29.489 --> 05:32.356
Adam, how did it feel
to cast your first vote?

05:32.425 --> 05:34.540
- Good.
- Who'd you vote for?

05:34.608 --> 05:36.153
I can't tell you that.

05:36.221 --> 05:37.228
Oh, come on, now.

05:37.297 --> 05:38.563
You really want four years of this?

05:38.631 --> 05:40.665
I want eight. He's a natural.

05:40.733 --> 05:42.215
He's a good actor.

05:42.537 --> 05:44.368
He might be more like her than you.

05:44.437 --> 05:46.137
- [Cellphone rings]
- Hi.

05:46.206 --> 05:47.338
[Chatter]

05:47.407 --> 05:49.173
Thank you, everyone.

05:49.242 --> 05:51.242
That's all
we’ll have time for right now.

05:51.311 --> 05:53.411
- Claire: What is it?
- ‭Nina.

05:53.479 --> 05:54.545
Oh, for the love of God.

05:54.614 --> 05:55.913
Okay, yeah. ‭It's election day.

05:55.982 --> 05:57.582
Can't she just give us one minute?

05:57.650 --> 05:59.116
So they got the guy in custody.

05:59.185 --> 06:01.085
They want Adam to identify him.

06:01.154 --> 06:04.555
[Chatter continues]

06:10.833 --> 06:12.230
[Breathing heavily] Well,
that one's not gonna work.

06:12.298 --> 06:14.131
- It will.
- It won't.

06:14.200 --> 06:16.300
You got a blow torch?

06:18.087 --> 06:19.604
Just have to wait until he gets back.

06:19.672 --> 06:21.205
That's not a good idea.

06:22.250 --> 06:23.707
I'll try and talk some sense into him.

06:24.477 --> 06:26.409
We both know
how this is gonna end for me,

06:26.479 --> 06:27.605
and it's not in a hug.

06:27.999 --> 06:29.471
I don't think he's a murderer.

06:30.350 --> 06:32.192
You have no idea what he is.

06:32.485 --> 06:34.352
The person you thought you knew
stopped existing

06:34.420 --> 06:36.359
when he kept
an 8-year-old child in a hole,

06:36.427 --> 06:37.639
and if you don't get that by now,

06:37.707 --> 06:39.523
you're a bigger idiot than I thought!

06:42.896 --> 06:44.387
That came out wrong.

06:50.974 --> 06:52.670
You're gonna get me out of here, Jane.

06:52.739 --> 06:53.905
How?

06:55.487 --> 06:56.606
You're gonna go back to the house

06:56.676 --> 06:58.743
and give the baby a bottle
so he's nice and tired

06:58.811 --> 07:00.378
and ready to sleep through anything,

07:00.446 --> 07:02.181
and then you're gonna get
a bucket of ice,

07:02.675 --> 07:05.230
some rubbing alcohol,
tight rubber bands,

07:05.255 --> 07:08.245
a bunch of clean towels,
and a lot more whiskey.

07:08.420 --> 07:09.198
Why?

07:09.656 --> 07:11.725
Because you're gonna cut off my thumbs.

07:12.125 --> 07:16.227
♪

07:20.293 --> 07:21.334
[Door closes]

07:22.276 --> 07:23.533
Can they see me?

07:23.861 --> 07:25.031
Nina: It's one-way glass.

07:25.898 --> 07:28.773
Can you think of a word
or phrase he would say to you?

07:28.841 --> 07:30.041
Something familiar?

07:32.446 --> 07:33.518
Bracelet.

07:35.315 --> 07:37.247
Bracelet. Key.

07:38.135 --> 07:39.681
What's that mean?

07:40.553 --> 07:42.306
He called the shackle my bracelet,

07:42.689 --> 07:44.362
and then he made me toss him the key.

07:50.296 --> 07:52.575
Woman: Number one, please step forward.

07:54.334 --> 07:57.835
Repeat the words "bracelet, key".

07:57.904 --> 07:59.166
Bracelet, key.

07:59.831 --> 08:01.974
Number two, please step forward.

08:02.633 --> 08:03.708
And the phrase.

08:03.776 --> 08:05.309
Bracelet, key.

08:05.378 --> 08:07.144
♪

08:07.213 --> 08:08.204
Step back.

08:09.641 --> 08:10.949
Number three.

08:14.954 --> 08:17.037
Bracelet, key.

08:21.728 --> 08:23.196
- Step back.
- ‭Ben: Wait.

08:24.069 --> 08:25.563
Do you want to make an ID?

08:26.226 --> 08:27.170
Is that him?

08:27.834 --> 08:30.801
♪

08:32.620 --> 08:33.563
No.

08:34.273 --> 08:35.308
What?

08:36.732 --> 08:37.828
That's not him.

08:38.378 --> 08:40.378
♪

08:40.446 --> 08:41.602
Why don't we take a break?

08:41.672 --> 08:43.240
I don't need a break.
Let's do the next one.

08:43.265 --> 08:44.648
I think you should take another look.

08:44.717 --> 08:46.479
That's not him. He's not in there.

08:49.203 --> 08:50.608
Woman: Meyer, I'm calling it.

08:50.677 --> 08:52.957
Let him take another look. We
know that he's been wrong before.

08:53.026 --> 08:54.221
- I don't need to.
- Look again.

08:54.290 --> 08:55.176
That's enough.

08:57.088 --> 08:58.872
I'd like to go home now.

08:59.232 --> 09:00.898
♪

09:02.311 --> 09:04.530
Just look at him... total focus,

09:04.911 --> 09:07.516
like Mosley hammering De La Hoya
in the 12th round.

09:07.585 --> 09:11.276
He devours those 1098s
with such precision and grace.

09:11.410 --> 09:12.676
Very funny, guys.

09:12.745 --> 09:13.911
Morning, everyone.

09:13.980 --> 09:16.099
Heck of a job
on that corporate return, Hank.

09:16.168 --> 09:17.804
- Really nice work.
- ‭Thanks, Ted.

09:17.873 --> 09:20.213
Might start throwing you more
of the heavy lifting come March.

09:20.620 --> 09:21.451
That'd be great.

09:21.519 --> 09:24.021
Hey, we're hitting up
Taco Dan's for lunch. You in?

09:24.090 --> 09:25.708
I've got stuff to do.

09:26.648 --> 09:29.860
Waitress with the stocked
dairy section totally wants you.

09:30.463 --> 09:33.063
Oh, well, [Chuckles] rain check.

09:34.208 --> 09:35.465
Mike: Impressive restraint.

09:35.534 --> 09:38.194
This is why we'll all
end up working for him.

09:40.373 --> 09:44.241
[Children yelling indistinctly]

09:45.945 --> 09:48.812
♪

10:08.501 --> 10:11.222
Coming up at noon,
a hot new exercise trend.

10:11.247 --> 10:12.558
See how belly dancing

10:12.627 --> 10:15.072
can help you say goodbye
to your belly roll.

10:15.141 --> 10:16.874
More information on this afternoon's

10:16.942 --> 10:18.615
three-car pileup on 295...

10:18.683 --> 10:21.251
what happened and how it will
affect your evening commute.

10:21.320 --> 10:22.623
And now let's go to weather

10:22.648 --> 10:25.249
with local meteorologist David Brown.

10:25.317 --> 10:26.417
♪

10:29.488 --> 10:32.956
[Dialing]

10:33.025 --> 10:36.401
[Ringing]

10:36.469 --> 10:37.906
Woman: News Channel Five.

10:38.731 --> 10:40.984
Hi, I'm calling
from the police station.

10:41.834 --> 10:43.669
I understand there's been a break

10:43.738 --> 10:46.200
in the Adam Warren kidnapping case.

10:46.739 --> 10:49.169
A suspect has been identified,

10:49.305 --> 10:52.302
and he may even be in custody by now.

10:52.666 --> 10:58.716
And the tip came
from Hank Asher... A-s-h-e-r.

10:58.784 --> 11:00.028
Thank you.

11:00.352 --> 11:02.786
[Telephone beeps]

11:05.196 --> 11:07.213
So you gonna want to order, or...

11:07.712 --> 11:09.645
Oh, sorry. Do you have a menu?

11:09.670 --> 11:11.345
We're more of a
‭"you tell me what you want,

11:11.370 --> 11:12.960
I tell you what you get" type place.

11:13.599 --> 11:15.461
Well, first, ‭I'm gonna be here awhile,

11:15.530 --> 11:17.456
so I'm gonna need this
to always be full,

11:17.525 --> 11:18.941
and do you have Wi-Fi?

11:19.271 --> 11:21.538
We don't get too many people
with computers in here.

11:21.607 --> 11:23.144
I'm guessing you're not a trucker.

11:23.212 --> 11:24.329
Mm, reporter.

11:24.398 --> 11:26.310
I'm about to break a very big story.

11:26.378 --> 11:28.303
I don't really read the papers too much.

11:28.781 --> 11:30.257
Well, you'll read this one.

11:30.326 --> 11:31.270
What's it about?

11:32.142 --> 11:34.951
Sex, lies, politics, family.

11:35.521 --> 11:37.885
I better keep ‭the coffee coming, then.

11:37.953 --> 11:39.855
I'm Sally if you need me.

11:40.726 --> 11:44.828
♪

11:51.694 --> 11:53.062
Thanks for coming in.

11:56.067 --> 11:57.158
Happy to help.

11:58.144 --> 12:00.813
Mr. Anderson, your jacket.

12:05.484 --> 12:06.859
You know, ‭I hope you find the guy.

12:07.019 --> 12:08.078
I really do.

12:09.000 --> 12:10.886
And relax, too.

12:11.518 --> 12:13.251
You got to find some joy in the job.

12:13.692 --> 12:15.495
That's what my partner says.

12:18.998 --> 12:20.189
Don't know him.

12:21.901 --> 12:23.534
[Indistinct conversations]

12:26.105 --> 12:27.271
[Sighs]

12:28.182 --> 12:30.072
When do they start counting
all the votes?

12:30.142 --> 12:32.542
- Not till the poles close.
- Oh.

12:33.126 --> 12:34.469
I never knew how it all worked.

12:37.636 --> 12:40.298
Did he make you wear them a lot?

12:41.587 --> 12:42.363
What?

12:43.796 --> 12:44.912
The bracelets.

12:46.571 --> 12:47.680
Not at first.

12:49.427 --> 12:50.998
When did it start?

12:52.417 --> 12:53.481
When we were older.

12:54.233 --> 12:55.804
When we started fighting back.

12:56.642 --> 12:58.272
And he did that to Adam, too?

12:59.264 --> 13:00.579
He fought back the most.

13:03.576 --> 13:05.342
[Sighs] ‭Are you sure?

13:07.489 --> 13:09.322
That he wasn't in that lineup?

13:10.615 --> 13:11.679
I'm sure.

13:12.244 --> 13:15.643
Because she was so convinced
that she had him.

13:17.028 --> 13:18.692
She's been wrong before.

13:21.961 --> 13:24.995
[Siren wails in distance]

13:25.064 --> 13:28.131
[Indistinct conversation]

13:28.200 --> 13:29.433
You hiding?

13:30.386 --> 13:32.201
There's press all over.
I'm not commenting.

13:33.434 --> 13:35.063
What the hell was that back there?

13:35.337 --> 13:36.537
That was the guy, John.

13:37.403 --> 13:38.909
You're losing your mind.

13:38.978 --> 13:40.037
Just trust me, okay?

13:40.417 --> 13:41.291
Trust you?

13:42.314 --> 13:44.748
You just made him relive
the worst moment of his life,

13:44.817 --> 13:46.268
and then you called him a liar.

13:46.293 --> 13:47.999
That was the guy who took your son!

13:48.193 --> 13:50.521
Well... he says it's not,

13:50.546 --> 13:52.091
so who ‭am I supposed to believe?

13:55.516 --> 13:56.510
Him.

13:57.815 --> 13:59.127
You believe him.

14:01.327 --> 14:03.347
- What's going on?
- Nothing.

14:13.345 --> 14:14.748
[Sighs]

14:33.269 --> 14:35.473
Don't come near my family again.

14:36.035 --> 14:38.902
♪

14:52.831 --> 14:53.903
[Car alarm chirps]

14:54.616 --> 14:59.156
♪

14:59.224 --> 15:02.596
[Cellphone beeping]

15:02.703 --> 15:05.337
Mr. Anderson, your jacket.

15:08.934 --> 15:11.668
♪

15:22.892 --> 15:25.300
Clements: One snip. Quick
and easy, below the joint.

15:26.273 --> 15:27.851
The cleaner it is, the easier it'll be

15:27.920 --> 15:29.755
to sew back on
‭when we get to a hospital.

15:31.181 --> 15:33.757
Put that down and look at me, Jane.

15:36.095 --> 15:39.409
You hit me on the head with the
business end of a frying pan.

15:39.478 --> 15:40.864
You got this.

15:42.935 --> 15:44.372
Come on. Get me out of here.

15:45.539 --> 15:46.748
I can't.

15:51.246 --> 15:52.542
I have a husband.

15:52.611 --> 15:54.208
Yeah, his name's Jonah.

15:55.392 --> 15:59.144
The last thing I said to him was
"I'll pick up the smoker fuel."

15:59.718 --> 16:01.451
What's that? ‭It's a bee thing.

16:01.520 --> 16:03.620
You have to smoke the hive
to harvest the honey.

16:03.689 --> 16:06.123
Very important to a beekeeper,
but it's not the last thing

16:06.191 --> 16:08.478
I wanted to have said
to the love of my life...

16:09.107 --> 16:11.228
the man who wakes up
singing in falsetto.

16:11.296 --> 16:12.462
I kid you not.

16:12.531 --> 16:15.665
"It's gonna be a bright,
bright sunshiny day."

16:15.734 --> 16:19.321
The idiot who asked me to marry
him three days after we met,

16:19.805 --> 16:22.039
and the sap who makes the same

16:22.107 --> 16:25.409
disgusting molasses
Christmas cookies every year

16:25.477 --> 16:28.368
because his grandmother
made them, and I eat them.

16:28.628 --> 16:32.564
Jane, I eat those cookies
because it makes him happy.

16:35.268 --> 16:38.898
I'm coming home with that smoker fuel,

16:38.967 --> 16:42.142
so cut off my damn thumbs.

16:42.895 --> 16:46.157
♪

16:46.182 --> 16:47.470
Do it, Jane.

16:48.067 --> 16:51.868
♪

16:58.110 --> 17:00.143
[Whispers] Just do it.

17:00.212 --> 17:01.978
[Screams]

17:07.487 --> 17:10.141
Hi, am I speaking to Angela Scott?

17:10.601 --> 17:12.874
Oh, it's... it's Mayor Claire Warren.

17:13.361 --> 17:15.618
Yes, [Chuckles] yes,
it really is. I'm fine.

